Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/Exceptio.name: exceptionDescription
Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/Exceptio.abstract: Exception Description Specifies the description of an exception.

Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/Exceptio.name: exceptionFatal
Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/Exceptio.abstract: Exception Fatal Specifies whether the exception was fatal. Bool value

Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/EventTra.name: category
Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/EventTra.abstract: Event Category Specifies the event category. Must not be empty.

Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/EventTra.name: action
Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/EventTra.abstract: Event Action Specifies the event action. Must not be empty.

Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/EventTra.name: value
Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/EventTra.abstract: Event Value Specifies the event value. Values must be non-negative.

Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/AppTrack.name: applicationName
Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/AppTrack.abstract: Application Name Specifies the application name. This field is required for any hit that has app related data (i.e., app version, app ID, or app installer ID). For hits sent to web properties, this field is optional.

Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/ScreenVi.name: screenName
Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/ScreenVi.abstract: Screen Name This parameter is optional on web properties, and required on mobile properties for screenview hits, where it is used for the ‘Screen Name’ of the screenview hit. On web properties this will default to the unique URL of the page by either using the &dl parameter as-is or assembling it from &dh and &dp.

Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/All.html.name: protocolVersion
Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/All.html.abstract: The Measurement Protocol version The current value is “1”. This will only change when there are changes made that are not backwards compatible.

Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/All.html.name: trackingID
Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/All.html.abstract: Tracking ID / Web Property ID The format is UA-XXXX-Y. All collected data is associated by this ID.

Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/All.html.name: dataSource
Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/All.html.abstract: Data Source Indicates the data source of the hit. Hits sent from analytics.js will have data source set to ‘web’; hits sent from one of the mobile SDKs will have data source set to ‘app’.

Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/All.html.name: clientID
Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/All.html.abstract: Client ID This field is required if User ID (uid) is not specified in the request. This anonymously identifies a particular user, device, or browser instance. For the web, this is generally stored as a first-party cookie with a two-year expiration. For mobile apps, this is randomly generated for each particular instance of an application install. The value of this field should be a random UUID (version 4) as described in http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc4122.txt.

Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/All.html.name: customDimension
Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/All.html.abstract: Custom Dimension Each custom dimension has an associated index. There is a maximum of 20 custom dimensions (200 for Analytics 360 accounts). The dimension index must be a positive integer between 1 and 200, inclusive.

Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/All.html.name: All
Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/All.html.abstract: Keys that availible for all hits in Google Analytics Measurement Protocol.

Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/ScreenVi.name: ScreenView
Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/ScreenVi.abstract: Keys that availible for Screen View hit in Google Analytics Measurement Protocol.

Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/AppTrack.name: AppTracking
Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/AppTrack.abstract: Keys that availible for App Tracking hit in Google Analytics Measurement Protocol.

Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/EventTra.name: EventTracking
Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/EventTra.abstract: Keys that availible for Event Tracking hit in Google Analytics Measurement Protocol.

Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/Exceptio.name: ExceptionsTracking
Structs/MeasurementProtocolKeys/Exceptio.abstract: Keys that availible for Exceptions Tracking hit in Google Analytics Measurement Protocol.
